Name: CSIRO
Description: Australia's national science research agency.

Name: Northern Territory Department of Infrastructure, Planning and Environment
Description: The Northern Territory Department of Infrastructure, Planning and Environment is now called the Department of Logistics and Infrastructure (DLI). It was previously named the Department of Infrastructure, Planning and Logistics (DIPL). The DLI was established in September 2024 by the Northern Territory Government. It focuses on infrastructure, logistics, and sustainable development across the Northern Territory.

Name: NT Fauna Atlas
Description: This is a comprehensive database of all known vertebrate fauna records, including mammals, birds, reptiles, frogs and fish, as well threatened invertebrates, for the Northern Territory.

Name: Canberra and National NatureMapr Network Incorporated
Description: NatureMapr empowers decision makers through citizen-supplied biodiversity data

Name: Department of Environment Tourism Science and Innovation
Description:
Our department recognises the enormous value a clean environment, innovative society and visitor economy, and vibrant culture contributes to our lives.

As a diverse organisation, the department brings together key areas of work to achieve our objectives for a better Queensland.

Name: WildNet platform
Description: WildNet is home to wildlife sightings, survey results, species profiles and multimedia.

Name: Qld Threatened Species Group
Description: Part of Department of the Environment, Tourism, Science and Innovation (DETSI)

Name: Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service
Description: Part of Qld DETSI

Name: SunWater
Description: Sunwater is a Queensland-based water service provider, making the most of the available water supply for our agriculture, urban and industrial customers.

Name: Reef Catchments
Description: Reef Catchments is the Natural Resource Management (NRM) organisation for the Mackay Whitsunday Isaac region. We facilitate change and work for long-term solutions to sustain, protect, and improve our region’s natural resources and environment, both now and into the future.

Name: Qld Department of Environment and Resource Management
Description: DERM was dissolved and transformed into the Department of Environment and Heritage Protection (EHP) in 2012

Name: Qld Department of Agriculture and Fisheries
Description: The Department of Agriculture and Fisheries (DAF) was officially dissolved and replaced by the Department of Primary Industries (DPI) on 1 November 2024, due to machinery of government changes.

Name: Gold Coast City Council
Description: The council of the Gold Coast

Name: Queensland-Naturalists-Club
Description: The Queensland Naturalists’ Club Inc aims to study all branches of natural history, to encourage the preservation and protection of native flora and fauna and their environments. We also focus on publishing worthwhile observations on natural history and record club activities.

Name: Mahogany Glider Recovery Team
Description: The Mahogany Glider Recovery Team (MGRT) provides advice and coordinates actions identified in the Mahogany Glider Recovery Plan. The MGRT includes representatives from organisations with a direct interest in the recovery of the Mahogany Glider, including those involved in funding and those participating in actions that support the recovery of the species.

Name: CSIRO
Description: Australia's national science research agency.

Name: Mary River Catchment Coordination Association
Description: The Mary River Catchment Coordination Association is a very active Integrated Catchment Management organisation overseen by the Mary River Catchment Coordinating Committee (MRCCC), which comprises interest sector representatives from 30 community, industry and government sectors with interests in sustainable natural resource management. Today the group reaches out to thousands of catchment residents through our stakeholder delegates and associated networks throughout the catchment.

Name: BirdLife Australia
Description: BirdLife Australia’s mission is to save birds. For over 120 years

Name: Qld Department of Transport and Main Roads
Description:
The Department of Transport and Main Roads moves and connects people, places, goods and services safely, efficiently and effectively across Queensland.
We plan, manage and deliver Queensland's integrated transport environment to achieve sustainable transport solutions for road, rail, air and sea.

Name: WBM Oceanics Australia
Description: Acquired by BTM in 2008

Name: EcoSmart Ecology
Description: EcoSmart Ecology is an emerging industry leader in ecological research, survey and assessment with a strong client focus and the highest commitment to quality. Use our balance of knowledge, skills and experience to assist in navigating through the array of environmental issues and statutory requirements facing ecological planners and developers.

Name: Lockyer Catchment Association Inc
Description: Organisation found in ABR but not online

Name: University of Queensland
Description: Ranked in the world's top 50, The University of Queensland is one of Australia's leading research and teaching institutions.

Name: WWF Australia
Description: At WWF-Australia we’ve been protecting nature’s wonders for more than 40 years. And now we’re working with communities, governments, companies and others not just to protect our natural world but to restore and regenerate it.

Name: Bribie Island Environmental Protection Association Inc
BirdLife Australia
Description: BirdLife Australia’s mission is to save birds. For over 120 years

Name: Biodiversity Assessment and Management (BAAM)
Description: BAAM was established in Brisbane in 2001 to provide terrestrial fauna ecology consulting services. Since that time the company has grown to include botanical expertise, ecological restoration and fauna spotting services. For projects requiring specific expertise we source contribution from within our significant network of ecological specialists to ensure the rigour of our work.

Name: Mackay Bird Observers Club of Australia
Description: Now part of BirdLife Australia

Name: Cooloola Coastcare
Description: Cooloola Coastcare Association is the Cooloola Coast's award winning Natural Resource Management group, registered with Queensland Water and Land Carers (QWALC) and supported by Gympie Regional Council through ratepayer's Environment Levy.

Name: NT Herbarium
Description:
A herbarium is a 'museum or library of plant specimens'. They are part of an international network dedicated to the study and identification of plants.

The NT Herbarium has a collection of 270,000 preserved plant specimens kept for reference and research.

Name: NT Department of Lands Planning and Environment
Description: The department includes the key functions that foster and protect the environment and natural resources in the Northern Territory.

Name: American Museum of Natural History
Description:
The American Museum of Natural History is one of the world’s preeminent scientific and cultural institutions.

Since its founding in 1869, the Museum has advanced its global mission to discover, interpret, and disseminate information about human cultures, the natural world, and the universe through a wide-ranging program of scientific research, education, and exhibition.

Name: Natural History Museum
Description:
The Natural History Museum is a world-class visitor attraction and leading science research centre.

We use our unique collections and unrivalled expertise to tackle the biggest challenges facing the world today.

We care for more than 80 million objects spanning billions of years and welcome more than five million visitors annually.

Name: Queensland Museum
Description: Queensland Museum is the keeping place for the State Collection, a magnificent assemblage of 1.2 million cultural objects, natural history specimens and geological treasures and more than 14 million research items. Every year, we bring our collections to life through fieldwork, contemporary acquisitions, world-class research and a dynamic program of exhibitions, workshops, talks, lectures and major events including World Science Festival Brisbane.

Name: Queensland Museum
Description: Queensland Museum is the keeping place for the State Collection, a magnificent assemblage of 1.2 million cultural objects, natural history specimens and geological treasures and more than 14 million research items. Every year, we bring our collections to life through fieldwork, contemporary acquisitions, world-class research and a dynamic program of exhibitions, workshops, talks, lectures and major events including World Science Festival Brisbane.

Name: Australian Museum
Description: The Australian Museum is an NSW Government organisation operating under the Department of Creative Industries

Name: Qld Department of Environment and Science
Description: This Department was renamed the Department of Environment, Tourism, Science & Innovation in early 2025.

Name: Western Australian Museum
Description:
The Western Australian Museum is the State's premier cultural organisation, housing WA's scientific and cultural collection.

For over 120 years the Museum has been making the State's natural and social heritage accessible and engaging through research, exhibition and public programs.

Today, the Museum has seven public locations across the state - and a Collection and Research Centre that houses more than eight million objects.

We use our unique collections and unrivalled expertise to tackle the biggest challenges facing the world today.

We care for more than 80 million objects spanning billions of years and welcome more than five million visitors annually.

Name: Macleay Museum
Description: This museum was formerly part of the University of Sydney but it has been abolished now and its contents transfered to the chau Chack Wing museum within the university.
